result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Jessica J Darden was found guilty of OWI (4th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Collection may include income assignment.

10:02 AM Defendant Jessica J Darden in court, in custody, with attorney Cassandra A Miller.   Alyssa M. Schaller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for plea and sentencing.
Defense acknowledges receipt of Amended Information and waives reading.  
NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
Court places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy. 

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Charges 1, 3, 4, and 5 are Dismissed and read in.
Count 6 is Dismissed by operation of law.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the court.

Court orders the following:
SENTENCE WITHHELD.

Term of Probation:  2 YEARS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Comply with all conditions of OWI Treatment Court;
*No operation of a motor vehicle with a valid driver's license;

CONDITION TIME:  300 DAYS; First 60 DAYS HUBER with release for work and childcare, The remainder of the condition time would be straight- time to be served only if not successful in the OWI treatment program.

D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

FINE:  $3,851
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to City of Waukesha Police Department. 
*To be paid as a Condition of Probation.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
